      • representativeId

        public static Query representativeId(String id)
        Creates a query that searches for clusters that contain a representative member with the given identifier.

        If the entry chosen to represent the cluster is from UniProtKB, then the id will be the protein identifier, e .g. CYC_HUMAN. If no UniProtKB entry is able to characterize the cluster, then a UniParc entry identifier will exist, e.g. UPI00052B5D80.

        Parameters:
        id - the identifier of representative member
        Returns:
        a query that will be run against the search engine

      • representativeAccession

        public static Query representativeAccession(String accession)
        Creates a query that searches for clusters that contain a representative member with the given accession.

        The accession can be that of a UniProtKB protein, e.g. P99999, when one is associated to the representative member, and/or the UniParc entry identifier, e.g. UPI00052B5D80.

        Parameters:
        accession - the accession of representative member
        Returns:
        a query that will be run against the search engine

      • representativeProteinName

        public static Query representativeProteinName(String name)
        Creates a query that searches for UniRef clusters holding representative members that contain the given protein name.

        The search allows you to provide partial names for searching. The partial search terms can occur anywhere within the protein name.

        Note: The vaguer the search terms the higher the amount of entries you will have to potentially process and filter out.

        Parameters:
        name - the protein name to search for
        Returns:
        a query that will be run against the search engine

      • representativeOrganismName

        public static Query representativeOrganismName(String name)
        Creates a query that searches for UniRef clusters holding representative members that contain the given organism name.

        The search tem can be the scientific name, the common name, or a synonym.

        The query allows you to provide partial names for searching. Terms should be whole words, i.e. bact will not hit Bacteria. An organism with spaces or forward slashes are good candidates for partial searches, e.g. searching for hanedai will hit the organism name Shewanella hanedai, or searching for Yamada will hit the organism name Variola virus (isolate Human/Japan/Yamada MS-2(A)/1946) (VARV) (Smallpox virus).

        Note: The vaguer the search terms the higher the amount of entries you will have to potentially process and filter out.

        Parameters:
        name - the name of the species to query
        Returns:
        a query that will be run against the search engine

      • representativeTaxonId

        public static Query representativeTaxonId(int taxId)
        Creates a query that searches for UniRef clusters holding representative members that contain the given NCBI taxonomic identifier.

        No partial searches are supported in this query.

        Parameters:
        taxId - an NCBI taxonomic identifier
        Returns:
        a query that will be run against the search engine
